question:
I have the following code, and it throws exception “b”. It seems that calling 
RhinoDoc.Create(null)
 is invalidating the object id for the sphere in the first doc, but I thought objects in separate docs should be separate. Any ideas what’s going on?


   var brep = new Sphere(Point3d.Origin, 1).ToBrep();
   var id = panel.m_Doc.Objects.Add(brep);
   if (panel.m_Doc.Objects.FindId(id) == null)
   {
       throw new Exception("a");
   }
   var test = RhinoDoc.Create(null);
   if (panel.m_Doc.Objects.FindId(id) == null)
   {
       throw new Exception("b");
   }

